    "does_not_license": "Does not license a binary AI / human authorship verdict. The score is a literature-anchored measurement against the Russell et al. 2026 long-form-fiction means; the framework ships no per-corpus thresholds as defaults and the verdict band is 'uncalibrated' until an operator supplies --threshold-low / --threshold-high derived from their own polarity check (see narrative_polarity_audit.py). Does not generalize to non-fiction registers without operator-side validation — several features (subplot integration, anachrony, frame narratives, sensory density) are not well-defined on essays, op-eds, or short-form prose. Does not substitute for Tier-1 variance, AIC-7/8/9 craft-pattern, or Binoculars audits; the paper's framing is that narrative-decision tells are *complementary* to stylistic tells, surviving LAMP-style rewriting that scrubs surface artifacts.",
